<br>
I do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  NOT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want to change from agnostic to worshipping Solusek Ro.  Back when I started playing (Just after release), all the deity stuff was just nonsense that didn't matter.  Now they have made it matter somewhat, and I don't really mind.<br>
<br>
I do not mind there being <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  SOME</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> deity-restricted items.  My only concern is that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ALL</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the items will be deity-restricted.  What would make me happy is the following:<br>
<br>
Solusek's Signet Ring of Service<br>
Deity: NONE<br>
Class: Wizard<br>
Race: Everyone but gnomes<br>
Stats: +10 STR, +15 INT, +100 HP, +100 MANA, +50 SV FIRE<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
Solusek's Ring of Blessings<br>
Deity: Solusek Ro<br>
Class: Wizard<br>
Race: Still no gnomes<br>
Stats: +11 STR, +16 INT, +10 CHA, +110 HP, +110 MANA, +55 SV FIRE<br>
<br>
Now, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ALL</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the quests should probably be FACTION-BASED.  The only thing different is that an Agnostic person would have to get <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ALLY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> faction with Solusek Ro to get the Signet Ring of Service.<br>
<br>
My wizard does not worship <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ANY</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;lesser being&quot;, but will form alliances.  My entire point is that deity worshipers should not get some insane ub3r l33t g3ar that others cannot have.  If EQ had deities from the beginning, and deity-restricted items in beta, then I wouldn't mind so much.<br>
<br>
